The property of 1 and 2 as TTA-UC annihilators are tested in THF solution (3.5 × 10–5 M) with platinum (II) octaethyl porphyrin (PtOEP, 10–4 M) as triplet sensitizer. Figure 3a reports the photoluminescence spectrum of the bicomponent solution under cw excitation at 532 nm. The laser stray light has been partially removed using a notch filter. A low-energy emission at 645 is detectable in both samples, due to incomplete energy transfer (ET) from excited sensitizers to annihilators triplets at the employed concentrations. These latter are kept low to avoid possible intermolecular interactions between annihilators that can affect the UC performance, but large enough to have a measurable ET yield ϕET\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
